00:27:12,572 --> 00:27:13,656
Yeah.

268
00:27:13,656 --> 00:27:16,910
There should have been a sensor camera in front of it. Did you bring it?

269
00:27:16,910 --> 00:27:19,921
What are you saying? There wasn't such a thing.

270
00:27:23,625 --> 00:27:27,461
I know Da Won would have installed it.

271
00:27:27,461 --> 00:27:28,545
What about the rucksack?

272
00:27:28,545 --> 00:27:31,593
Have you checked her rucksack? There should've been a notepad.

273
00:27:31,593 --> 00:27:35,094
Yi Kang... I took all of her belongings to the police.

274
00:27:35,094 --> 00:27:36,696
Then, bye.

275
00:27:48,083 --> 00:27:50,266
- A ranger's notepad?
- Correct.

276
00:27:50,266 --> 00:27:54,197
With Da Won's name on it. She always carried it with her to the mountains.

277
00:27:54,197 --> 00:27:59,327
I took all her belongings to the main department, but there was no notepad.

278
00:27:59,327 --> 00:28:02,388
Not in her rucksack or pockets.

279
00:28:14,780 --> 00:28:16,860
[Lee Da Won, Haedong Station]

280
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:22,620
[Geombawi (Black) Rock, Saema Valley, Moojin Neighborhood]

281
00:28:23,830 --> 00:28:26,650
[Pine forest, Moojin Neighborhood]

282
00:28:53,323 --> 00:28:55,759
If it wasn't Hyun Jo...

283
00:28:55,759 --> 00:28:59,454
Who left the mark and why?

284
00:29:47,644 --> 00:29:49,812
Be careful, everyone.

285
00:32:03,129 --> 00:32:05,672
I need to see Hyun Jo.

286
00:32:05,673 --> 00:32:07,884
The one that I trusted the most...

287
00:32:11,512 --> 00:32:15,141
My colleague who cherished the mountain with all his heart.

288
00:32:18,686 --> 00:32:20,688
I must see him.

289
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:25,734
Hyun Jo...

290
00:32:25,735 --> 00:32:27,737
Are you there?

291
00:32:29,072 --> 00:32:31,282
Answer me if you're up there.

292
00:32:33,293 --> 00:32:37,163
Tell me what you saw and what you know.

293
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:44,940
[2019]

294
00:34:16,913 --> 00:34:18,748
I feel better now, thanks to you.

295
00:34:18,748 --> 00:34:21,609
I won't need an ambulance. Thanks.

296
00:34:21,609 --> 00:34:25,280
I thought you were too sick to walk?

297
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:28,549
Yes, I was, but I'm all better now.

298
00:34:28,549 --> 00:34:30,484
Or maybe you faked it this whole time.

299
00:34:30,485 --> 00:34:32,303
What?

300
00:34:32,303 --> 00:34:34,372
What do you take me for?

301
00:34:34,372 --> 00:34:38,293
That's what I want to ask you. Do you think we're a taxi service?

302
00:34:38,293 --> 00:34:42,838
If you went up there by yourself. You should be able to come down, too.

303
00:34:43,381 --> 00:34:46,192
Do you know where your paychecks come from?

304
00:34:46,192 --> 00:34:49,862
It's money from the pockets of citizens like me.

305
00:34:49,862 --> 00:34:52,999
So don't even get started.

306
00:34:58,771 --> 00:35:03,517
I'll let you off today since I'm busy.

307
00:35:03,518 --> 00:35:07,488
- Ugh, seriously!
- Senior, calm down.

308
00:35:07,488 --> 00:35:09,424
It's a good thing that he's not actually sick.

309
00:35:09,424 --> 00:35:12,410
How can you say that in this situation?

310
00:35:13,010 --> 00:35:14,700
Well...

311
00:35:15,371 --> 00:35:17,949
Let's just say I had a tough training session.

312
00:35:21,994 --> 00:35:23,880
- Let me see.
- Ouch.

313
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:24,996
Goodness...

314
00:35:24,997 --> 00:35:27,007
Ouch. It hurts—

315
00:35:28,493 --> 00:35:32,055
So I told you not to carry him. You brought this onto yourself.

316
00:35:32,055 --> 00:35:33,531
That hurts!

317
00:35:33,531 --> 00:35:34,966
It's fine...

318
00:35:36,242 --> 00:35:37,827
Seo Yi Kang, where are you?

319
00:35:37,827 --> 00:35:41,080
There's been an SOS report one kilometer from Oerae Valley.

320
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:44,041
We've already mobilized twice today. Isn't there any other team?

321
00:35:44,041 --> 00:35:48,087
All other teams are on their way. Plus, we have quite a number of day-offs.

322
00:35:48,087 --> 00:35:51,190
The victim sprained his leg badly and is in a lot of pain.

323
00:35:53,952 --> 00:35:56,604
All right. We'll mobilize.

324
00:35:59,791 --> 00:36:02,894
- What are you doing?
- What? About mobilizing?

325
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:05,964
Or about helping you up?

326
00:36:05,964 --> 00:36:07,340
If that's not it...

327
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:08,916
This?

328
00:36:13,129 --> 00:36:17,141
You touched my leg so we're equal now.

329
00:36:19,327 --> 00:36:20,961
Let's go!

330
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:30,930
I shouldn't be so nice to him.

331
00:36:31,856 --> 00:36:35,151
Hey! Give me my rucksack!

332
00:36:37,987 --> 00:36:39,638
Goo Yeong.

333
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:43,835
When it's uphill,

334
00:36:43,835 --> 00:36:46,871
it's better to walk on the balls of your feet.

335
00:36:51,834 --> 00:36:53,294
Are you all right?

336
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:55,670
I'm fine.

337
00:36:55,671 --> 00:36:57,890
Should we have a water break?

338
00:37:02,729 --> 00:37:04,997
You're sweating a lot.

339
00:37:09,769 --> 00:37:12,062
Your shoelaces need to be tighter, too.

340
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:14,356
I think we did enough for today.

341
00:37:14,357 --> 00:37:16,625
Should we call it a day?

342
00:37:18,035 --> 00:37:19,996
You said you'd help me train.

343
00:37:19,996 --> 00:37:22,106
This is too easy.

344
00:37:23,916 --> 00:37:26,993
Didn't you say you know a cool place up there?

345
00:37:26,994 --> 00:37:28,578
Let's go there.

346
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:31,648
- Just up to there.
- Okay.

347
00:37:33,709 --> 00:37:35,861
Which way do we go?

348
00:37:38,381 --> 00:37:40,157
- Goo Yeong!
- Straight this way.

349
00:37:40,157 --> 00:37:41,926
- Here?
- Yup.

350
00:37:47,807 --> 00:37:49,766
- How much water did you drink?
- Not much, but...

351
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:52,144
- I want to pee.
- You want to pee?

352
00:37:55,398 --> 00:37:58,608
- Oh, I'm worn out.
- We're almost there.

353
00:37:58,609 --> 00:38:01,469
- Are you good?
- Yeah.

354
00:38:03,572 --> 00:38:07,034
Not many people know about this place.

355
00:38:07,535 --> 00:38:09,561
It's slippery here.

356
00:38:26,429 --> 00:38:28,805
Isn't this great?

357
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:31,717
It opens up your chest!

358
00:38:44,497 --> 00:38:46,474
If you come up here in the evening,

359
00:38:46,474 --> 00:38:48,784
the sun sets right over there.

360
00:38:49,335 --> 00:38:52,630
And the moon from over there, they hang side by side on the horizon.

361
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:54,457
It's beautiful.

362
00:38:56,342 --> 00:38:57,843
Wow...

363
00:38:58,794 --> 00:39:01,889
It's my first time coming all the way up to the ridge.

364
00:39:06,769 --> 00:39:09,313
I feel...

365
00:39:10,915 --> 00:39:13,151
I feel like a real ranger now.

366
00:39:13,151 --> 00:39:16,270
Why do you say that?

367
00:39:17,046 --> 00:39:19,814
It's always bothered me.

368
00:39:19,815 --> 00:39:22,410
I can't climb the mountain,

369
00:39:22,410 --> 00:39:24,861
I only cause inconvenience to others.

370
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:25,904
No.

371
00:39:25,905 --> 00:39:30,901
We can mobilize safely all thanks to your great work in the office.

372
00:39:32,795 --> 00:39:35,673
Take me to your training more often.

373
00:39:35,673 --> 00:39:37,958
I want to see many other places.

374
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:43,798
Just say when. Let's visit all of them.

375
00:39:45,007 --> 00:39:45,975
Okay.

376
00:39:45,975 --> 00:39:49,228
And I'll teach you about the rope thrower later.

377
00:39:49,228 --> 00:39:51,355
You can try rope climbing, too.

378
00:39:52,481 --> 00:39:54,317
I don't think I can.

379
00:39:54,317 --> 00:39:57,061
Why not? You're a ranger.

380
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:00,689
Right, I'm a ranger.

381
00:40:06,329 --> 00:40:09,681
I brought some snacks, Senior.

382
00:40:09,681 --> 00:40:11,458
Would you like to have them now?

383
00:40:11,458 --> 00:40:13,444
Sure!

384
00:40:15,521 --> 00:40:18,941
My mom's coming for this Mountain Spirit Ritual.

385
00:40:20,134 --> 00:40:23,303
She says she wants to meet up with you.

386
00:40:23,303 --> 00:40:25,397
Is that okay?

387
00:40:29,852 --> 00:40:32,146
Of course, it's okay.

388
00:40:35,724 --> 00:40:38,477
- Let me bring some water.
- Yeah.

389
00:40:54,794 --> 00:40:56,750
Here, drink some water.

390
00:40:56,750 --> 00:40:58,240
Yes.

391
00:41:05,990 --> 00:41:09,150
