397
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:46,740
[Jo Dae Jin: On Duty | Day off]
[Park Il Hae: Day off]
[Jung Goo Yeong: Day off]

398
00:41:46,740 --> 00:41:48,860
[Jo Dae Jin: On Duty | Day off]
[Park Il Hae: Day off]
[Jung Goo Yeong: Day off]

399
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:50,330
[Jo Dae Jin: On Duty | Day off]
[Park Il Hae: Day off]
[Jung Goo Yeong: Day off]

400
00:41:50,330 --> 00:41:53,468
Yes. Oh...

401
00:41:53,468 --> 00:41:56,062
The banner for the promotion booth isn't here yet.

402
00:41:56,062 --> 00:41:58,857
Okay. Call me when it's ready.

403
00:41:58,857 --> 00:42:04,004
Stuffed moon bears, pin buttons, face paint...

404
00:42:04,004 --> 00:42:06,148
I brought them all.

405
00:42:07,033 --> 00:42:08,992
Haedong Ranger Station.

406
00:42:08,992 --> 00:42:12,203
PR? Promotion booklets?

407
00:42:12,203 --> 00:42:14,748
I don't know. What's wrong?

408
00:42:14,748 --> 00:42:17,167
All right. I'll talk to the captain.

409
00:42:17,167 --> 00:42:19,186
Okay.

410
00:42:22,565 --> 00:42:24,549
Have our ancestors...

411
00:42:24,549 --> 00:42:28,562
really been doing this ritual for thousands of years?

412
00:42:29,597 --> 00:42:31,848
It'll get crazy busy for the next few days.

413
00:42:31,848 --> 00:42:36,962
A lot of people will come to watch the band and folk wrestling and many more...

414
00:42:36,962 --> 00:42:39,397
We worship them with all our might,

415
00:42:39,397 --> 00:42:41,441
but the mountain spirit is merciless.

416
00:42:41,441 --> 00:42:44,486
We could use fewer accidents.

417
00:42:44,486 --> 00:42:46,738
Mountain spirit's not the only one up there.

418
00:42:46,738 --> 00:42:48,782
Grandma told me a long time ago,

419
00:42:48,782 --> 00:42:53,178
that the evil spirit comes before the mountain spirit.

420
00:42:54,263 --> 00:42:57,174
Back then I thought it was all nonsense,

421
00:42:58,501 --> 00:43:03,550
but seeing you... I think it could be true.

422
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:18,803
Crappy weather today.

423
00:43:18,803 --> 00:43:19,813
I don't want to go to school.

424
00:43:19,813 --> 00:43:22,023
What you see here

425
00:43:22,023 --> 00:43:25,485
are terraced rice fields,

426
00:43:25,485 --> 00:43:28,196
which are made by cutting mountain slopes,

427
00:43:28,196 --> 00:43:32,890
and can still be found in various areas of Jirisan.

428
00:43:48,550 --> 00:43:49,917
What are you doing?

429
00:43:49,918 --> 00:43:54,581
If this hurts, imagine how much a broken stem would hurt.

430
00:43:55,474 --> 00:43:57,142
Give me your name.

431
00:43:57,142 --> 00:44:00,011
You will get no points for this visit.

432
00:44:00,846 --> 00:44:03,857
Screw you! You're just a guide.

433
00:44:03,857 --> 00:44:07,235
You're being rude in every way.

434
00:44:07,235 --> 00:44:11,039
- Give me your name!
- What the heck.

435
00:44:14,301 --> 00:44:16,203
What?

436
00:44:22,751 --> 00:44:25,487
You used to be the Chief of the National Park,

437
00:44:25,487 --> 00:44:28,465
but now you're being treated with disrespect.

438
00:44:28,465 --> 00:44:30,884
Do you still want to do this work?

439
00:44:31,552 --> 00:44:33,678
That sort of prejudice is the problem.

440
00:44:33,678 --> 00:44:36,681
There's no high and low at work.

441
00:44:36,681 --> 00:44:41,378
I heard you've been appointed as the Chairman of the Preservation Committee.

442
00:44:44,555 --> 00:44:47,826
I can't just sit back and watch until things work well.

443
00:44:47,826 --> 00:44:49,335
Things are a total disaster.

444
00:44:49,335 --> 00:44:53,860
The new Chief Park is nice but way too soft.

445
00:44:58,804 --> 00:45:02,324
What is it this time?

446
00:45:02,324 --> 00:45:05,850
What's troubling you now and made you come here?

447
00:45:13,552 --> 00:45:16,221
When do you think...

448
00:45:16,221 --> 00:45:19,230
we can quit this work?

449
00:45:22,686 --> 00:45:26,189
Is it because your daughter came back?

450
00:45:26,189 --> 00:45:29,360
Are you trying to reconnect with your daughter?

451
00:45:31,837 --> 00:45:34,447
This job, you can't take it just because you want.

452
00:45:34,447 --> 00:45:37,951
Or quit any time you want.

453
00:45:37,951 --> 00:45:40,887
It involves saving people's lives.

454
00:45:41,872 --> 00:45:43,831
That's right.

455
00:45:43,831 --> 00:45:46,793
Saving people's lives is our job.

456
00:45:46,793 --> 00:45:52,404
But I'm seeing more dead people than live ones.

457
00:45:52,404 --> 00:45:54,960
Who are you whining to?

458
00:45:55,569 --> 00:45:59,297
Go and patrol some more if you have time to complain.

459
00:46:04,411 --> 00:46:09,110
If that's what you're here for, I'm leaving.

460
00:46:17,658 --> 00:46:19,510
Do you remember him?

461
00:46:19,510 --> 00:46:23,010
[Chairperson Yang Geun Tak]
[Jirisan Cable Car Development Committee]

462
00:46:23,930 --> 00:46:25,748
That's right.

463
00:46:25,748 --> 00:46:28,820
He's come back to the mountain.

464
00:46:34,867 --> 00:46:38,011
The mountain spirit will be infuriated once again.

465
00:46:42,030 --> 00:46:50,010
[Campaign to establish a Jingye Village to Deokseoryeong cable car]

466
00:46:50,010 --> 00:46:51,450
[Cable Car]

467
00:46:51,450 --> 00:46:53,376
Please vote.

468
00:46:53,376 --> 00:46:55,336
Will this be okay?

469
00:46:55,336 --> 00:46:58,639
Of course, it's Jirisan.

470
00:46:58,639 --> 00:47:02,093
If we put the cable car straight this way, we'll minimize the damage to the mountain.

471
00:47:02,093 --> 00:47:05,146
Hi, please give it a look.

472
00:47:05,146 --> 00:47:07,840
Hi, here's one for you.

473
00:47:09,168 --> 00:47:11,377
Cable cars on Jirisan?

474
00:47:11,377 --> 00:47:14,756
Please have some tea before you go up.

475
00:47:14,756 --> 00:47:16,507
- Cable cars?
- Yes.

476
00:47:16,507 --> 00:47:20,695
If we only have the cable cars installed, we can all reach the top of Jirisan in ten minutes.

477
00:47:20,695 --> 00:47:23,573
No more unnecessary accidents from hiking.

478
00:47:23,573 --> 00:47:26,718
But the mountain will be brutally destroyed.

479
00:47:27,853 --> 00:47:30,820
Here. Please go inside.

480
00:47:36,862 --> 00:47:39,572
Are you determined to ruin this mountain?

481
00:47:39,572 --> 00:47:42,408
Why do you keep doing this?

482
00:47:42,408 --> 00:47:45,828
Ruin it? Jirisan is where I grew up.

483
00:47:45,828 --> 00:47:47,580
This is all for the mountain.

484
00:47:47,580 --> 00:47:51,167
If the Jirisan cable car construction begins, the whole ecology will be destroyed.

485
00:47:51,167 --> 00:47:52,502
Is that for the mountain?

486
00:47:52,502 --> 00:47:56,798
Installing cable cars and blocking the trails is better for environmental protection.

487
00:47:56,798 --> 00:47:58,232
And not just for the mountain.

488
00:47:58,232 --> 00:48:02,060
Nearby residents will benefit from it also.

489
00:48:04,515 --> 00:48:06,725
Black Bridge Valley Village.

490
00:48:08,102 --> 00:48:10,053
Have you forgotten?

491
00:48:11,230 --> 00:48:16,080
Have you forgotten all that's happened there?

492
00:48:21,448 --> 00:48:25,130
I'll never let that happen again.

493
00:48:27,413 --> 00:48:29,631
I will stop this.

494
00:48:34,670 --> 00:48:36,337
It's for real this time.

495
00:48:36,337 --> 00:48:38,673
Cable cars are coming in.

496
00:48:38,673 --> 00:48:40,174
That's even worse.

497
00:48:40,174 --> 00:48:45,187
They should choose Haedong Village. We're bigger and better known than Jingye Village.

498
00:48:45,187 --> 00:48:46,823
- Yes.
- You're right.

499
00:48:46,823 --> 00:48:49,784
Let's go talk to the person in charge tomorrow.

500
00:48:49,784 --> 00:48:53,204
Yeah. We know Chairman Yang Geun Tak.

501
00:48:53,204 --> 00:48:54,890
- Yes!
- Let's do that.

502
00:48:54,890 --> 00:48:57,430
- Let's go then.
- Yes, let's.

503
00:48:58,361 --> 00:49:02,405
Have they already forgotten the mess from before?

504
00:49:02,405 --> 00:49:06,710
Wish they'd stop being so greedy. Those people.

505
00:49:31,852 --> 00:49:35,820
The ritual has begun.

506
00:49:56,101 --> 00:49:58,912
Hello!

507
00:49:58,912 --> 00:50:01,081
Please help!

508
00:50:08,180 --> 00:50:11,849
I've been feeling sick. Is your phone working?

509
00:50:11,849 --> 00:50:14,644
Mine has no signal.

510
00:50:14,644 --> 00:50:18,373
Why would mine work if yours doesn't?

511
00:50:21,084 --> 00:50:25,263
I'm sorry, but can you please help me?

512
00:50:25,263 --> 00:50:28,899
I'd appreciate it if you could take me

513
00:50:28,899 --> 00:50:31,945
to the ridge up there where the people are.

514
00:50:31,945 --> 00:50:34,939
Do you think I have nothing better to do? I'm busy.

515
00:50:34,939 --> 00:50:35,948
Then,

516
00:50:35,949 --> 00:50:40,253
could you let the rangers know that I'm here?

517
00:50:40,253 --> 00:50:41,946
Jeez, lady.

518
00:50:41,946 --> 00:50:45,341
Do you want me to take myself in for illegal hiking?

519
00:50:45,341 --> 00:50:48,562
I'll get kicked out of here too, if I tell the rangers.

520
00:50:52,332 --> 00:50:56,119
I'll make a report on my way down, once I'm done with my business.

521
00:50:58,472 --> 00:51:03,531
Don't be so harsh on another hiker.

522
00:51:03,531 --> 00:51:06,688
Why are you even here if you can't climb?

523
00:51:10,192 --> 00:51:12,660
I just don't understand.

524
00:52:00,083 --> 00:52:03,094
How on earth...

